Interface ReadableMemoryProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FileMemoryProvider
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ReadableMemoryProvider
    Provides read access to the memory of a process via a stream.

    • Method Detail

      • openRead

        java.nio.channels.SeekableByteChannel openRead(int pid)
                                        throws java.io.IOException
        Opens a readable SeekableByteChannel to the memory of the specified process.
        Parameters:
        pid - The ID of the process.
        Returns:
        a readable, non-null SeekableByteChannel to the memory of the specified process.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the process does not exist, privileges are insufficient or the channel cannot be opened for other reasons.
